The paper focuses on cybersecurity awareness in African countries, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cybercrime (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the implementation of national awareness campaigns, which involves social and information sciences (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SE) to develop effective campaigns. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of user and executive awareness, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
